     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA01d043n1-ptr" id="PJA01d043n1">1</a>
      
   <p>This Inventory was required by the grant of probate, 10 July 1761, to be presented to the court on or before 10 Oct.; see above, Will of Deacon John Adams, &amp;c., under date of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-01-02-0027" class="document">8 Jan. 176029 April 1774</a>.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA01d043n2-ptr" id="PJA01d043n2">2</a>
      
   <p>Cran: An iron instrument, laid across the fire, reaching from the ribs of the grate to the hinder part of it, for the purpose of supporting a pot or kettle (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Oxford English Dictionary&lt;/i&gt;, Oxford, 1933; 12 vols. and supplement. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">OED</span></span>).</p>

